To write a good requirement, you must write it as a complete sentence, with a subject and a predicate (usually a verb). The
subject&amp;nbsp;is an Actor, a stakeholder, the system under development, or a design entity that is related to the
requirement. The predicate specifies a condition, action, or intended result that is done for, by, with, or to the
subject.&lt;/span></mainDescription>
